-- Ukrainian Unit of Erste Bank to Offer Loans for Energy Projects
-- B y   K a t e r y n a   C h o u r s i n a
-- 2011-12-29T14:48:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-29/ukrainian-unit-of-erste-bank-to-offer-loans-for-energy-projects.html
The Ukrainian unit of  Erste Group
Bank AG (EBS)  will increase authorized capital 10 million hryvnia
($1.24 million) in a private placement of shares.  The share placement will take place between March 14 and
April 2, according to a decision at a  shareholders’ meeting , the
Kiev-based bank, said today in an e-mailed statement. The bank’s
capital after the increase will be 1.38 billion hryvnia, the
statement says.  “The authorized capital increase will support the bank’s
stability and help us remain a reliable financial partner,”
Pavel Cetkovsky, Erste’s chief executive officer in Ukraine,
said in the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kateryna Choursina in Kiev at 
